ct in the template (not a custom component).\r\n\r\nHere's a simple fiddle illustrating the issue:\r\nhttps://jsfiddle.net/33df9qu8/3/\r\n\r\n![Custom select bug](http://i.imgur.com/hGrGcNM.png)\r\n\r\nIf you uncomment the option with a null optionId in my fiddle:\r\n\r\n{ text: 'Not selected', optionId: null },\r\n\r\n...the select behaves perfectly fine and selects that option. But that's not really a workaround as it forces us to add a null option and changes our UX.\r\n\r\nIt may be related to these similar issues here:\r\nhttps://github.com/vuejs/vue/issues/1008\r\nhttps://github.com/vuejs/vue/issues/3673\r\n\r\n### Vue.js version\r\n2.1.10\r\n\r\n### Chrome version\r\n55.0.2883.95 (64-bit)\r\n\r\n### Reproduction Link\r\nhttps://jsfiddle.net/33df9qu8/3/\r\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vuejs/vue/issues/4810/reactions","total_count":2,"+1":2,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vuejs/vue/issues/4810/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed"}},"event":"cross-referenced"}]